The SAPS member was gunned down outside his Wallacedene home shortly after 5am on Monday morning. CAPE TOWN - A police officer has been shot and killed in Kraaifontein.The South African Police Service member was gunned down outside his Wallacedene home shortly after 5am on Monday.The 35-year-old constable, stationed at Sea Border Unit at Table Bay Harbour, was off duty at the time.The police's Andre Traut says his firearm was stolen. This morning at about 5:20am an off-duty police officer and 35-year-old constable stationed at the Sea Border Unit at Table Bay Harbour was shot, killed and robbed of his service pistol in Wallacedene, Kraaifontein. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)